Title: Series: Ceiling Paintings from the Jesuits' Church in Antwerp
Description: Plate 5: The Triumph of Joseph in Egypt; Joseph in a chariot pulled by four horses, the animal at far left held by a groom by its bridle, two trumpeting putti in lower right, a classical temple beyond; octagonal composition; after Peter Paul Rubens. 1747 Etching and engraving
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of thirty-six, for comment see 1921,411.26. For the red chalk drawing by Jacob de Wit see 1921,0411.31.
Bibliographic references: Schneevoogt 1873 / Catalogue des estampes gravées d'après P.P.Rubens (212.10.13)
